# Floorplan + Obstacle Detection Integration

Merge the two independently-finished subsystems — the **floorplan parsing** (Agentic-RAG 5-agent pipeline) and the **obstacle detection** (EnhancedObstacleDetector, DFPN, RiskEngine) — into a single cohesive AidGPT experience inside [main.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py).

The user can:
1. **Run obstacle detection alone** (as today — always active)
2. **Open a Floorplan Tab** (`P` key) which runs the pipeline in the background and shows a rich side panel with the parsed map, navigation steps, and safety status
3. The parsed **nav steps** are also fed into the existing navigation guidance panel (press `N`) so the blind user hears and sees floor-plan-aware routing *on top of* real-time obstacle alerts

---

## Proposed Changes

---

### ApplicationState

#### [MODIFY] [application_state.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/core/application_state.py)

Add a new **Floorplan** block of state fields (after the DFPN block):

```python
# Floorplan parsing / Agentic-RAG integration
self.floorplan_mode: bool = False          # panel visible (toggle 'P')
self.floorplan_running: bool = False       # pipeline thread active
self.floorplan_image_path: str = ""        # last loaded image
self.floorplan_start: str = ""
self.floorplan_destination: str = ""
self.floorplan_result = None               # PipelineResult when done
self.floorplan_nav_index: int = 0          # current step
self.floorplan_status: str = "idle"        # idle | running | done | error
self.floorplan_error: str = ""
self.floorplan_panel_frame: Optional[np.ndarray] = None
```

---

### UI — New Floorplan Panel

#### [NEW] [floorplan_panel.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/ui/floorplan_panel.py)

Renders a 400-px-wide side panel with:
- **Header** — "FLOORPLAN" title + status badge (IDLE / RUNNING / DONE / ERROR)
- **Route banner** — `Start → Destination` with node count
- **Progress indicator** — animated spinner while pipeline runs; success/fail icon when done
- **Current Step card** — the active nav step with action, sensory feedback, confirmation
- **Step list** — scrollable numbered list of all nav steps (up to 8 visible at once)
- **Safety badge** — SAFE (green) / UNSAFE (orange) from the Safety Evaluator
- **Hazards** — top 3 hazards from safety report
- **Controls footer** — key hints (`P` close, `←/→` step, `Enter` speak step)

> All rendering is pure OpenCV (no GUI libs), matching the existing panel style.

---

### Core — Floorplan Manager

#### [MODIFY] [main.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py)

Add a `FloorplanManager` inner class / object on [Application](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py#72-1155) with:

| Method | Description |
|---|---|
| [load(image_path, start, dest)](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/cli.py#30-46) | Kicks off [run_pipeline(...)](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/Agentic/orchestrator.py#106-448) in a daemon thread; sets `state.floorplan_running=True` |
| `_pipeline_worker(...)` | Background thread: calls `orchestrator.run_pipeline`, writes result to `state.floorplan_result`, sets status to `done` or `error` |
| `next_step() / prev_step()` | Advance `state.floorplan_nav_index` |
| `get_current_step()` | Returns current `NavStep` |

Wiring points in [main.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py):
1. **[initialize_components](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py#202-280)** — instantiate `FloorplanManager`
2. **[_prepare_display_frame](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py#491-602)** — when `state.floorplan_mode`, composite floorplan panel on the right
3. **[_resize_window_for_side_by_side](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py#654-682)** — add case for floorplan mode
4. **[_on_inference_complete](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py#334-378)** — if floorplan done AND floorplan has current step, prepend that step's `action` text to `state.last_navigation_text` so the existing nav panel + TTS surfaces it automatically

---

### UI — Input Handler

#### [MODIFY] [input_handler.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/ui/input_handler.py)

Add key bindings:
| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `P` | Toggle `state.floorplan_mode` |
| `←` (left arrow = 81) | `floorplan_manager.prev_step()` when floorplan active |
| `→` (right arrow = 83) | `floorplan_manager.next_step()` when floorplan active |
| `Enter` | Speak current floorplan nav step aloud if floorplan active |

> [handle_keyboard](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/ui/input_handler.py#37-169) will receive `floorplan_manager` as an optional kwarg (same pattern as `detection_engine`).

---

### Startup Integration (argument + launch helper)

#### [MODIFY] [core/args.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/core/args.py)

Add optional CLI args:
```
--floorplan-image  PATH    Floor-plan image to load at startup
--floorplan-start  ROOM    Starting room name
--floorplan-dest   ROOM    Destination room name
```

If all three are provided at startup, `FloorplanManager.load(...)` is called automatically after initialization.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Two UX decisions need your input before I code this up:**
>
> 1. **Startup vs on-demand loading** — Should the floorplan pipeline auto-run when `--floorplan-image` args are provided, or should the user always press `P` first (and then a sub-dialog/path is needed)? I plan to *auto-run on startup if args are given, and show an "idle, press Enter to load" prompt otherwise*.
>
> 2. **Key for floorplan toggle** — `P` is currently unused. Does `P` work for you, or would you prefer a different key? (Current used keys: q, p-pause, d, m, b, g, t, v, s, k, j, o, u, l, h, y, a, n, f, c)
>
> Wait — `p` = pause. I'll use `Ctrl+P` or reassign. Suggest: **`[`** (open bracket) — easy to press. Alternatively, accept the user's preference.

> [!NOTE]
> The floorplan pipeline makes LLM calls (OpenAI / Claude) and takes **10–60 seconds**. The app stays fully responsive during this time (background thread). The panel shows an animated spinner while waiting.

