cd c:\Tim\AIDGPT\AidGPT
python -c "from ui.floorplan_panel import render_floorplan_panel; import numpy as np; p = render_floorplan_panel(720, None); print(p.shape)"
```
Expected: prints [(720, 400, 3)](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/main.py#965-1102) with no errors.

### Automated (state field check)
```bash
cd c:\Tim\AIDGPT\AidGPT
python -c "from core.application_state import ApplicationState; s = ApplicationState(); print(s.floorplan_mode, s.floorplan_status)"
```
Expected: prints `False idle`.

### Manual — Obstacle detection unaffected
1. `python main.py` (no extra args)
2. Verify detection boxes, depth map (M), nav panel (N) all work as before.
3. Press `[` — panel should appear with "IDLE — no floorplan loaded" message.
4. Press `[` again — panel disappears.

### Manual — Full floorplan pipeline
1. Have a floorplan image ready, e.g. [C:\Tim\AIDGPT\AidGPT\alt\dataset\floorplan\images\MP-860-3L.png](file:///Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/alt/dataset/floorplan/images/MP-860-3L.png)
2. `python main.py --floorplan-image "C:\Tim\AIDGPT\AidGPT\alt\dataset\floorplan\images\MP-860-3L.png" --floorplan-start "Hall" --floorplan-dest "Kitchen"`
3. The floorplan panel should appear automatically showing **RUNNING** with a spinner.
4. After ~30s the panel updates to **DONE**, shows nav steps, route, and safety status.
5. Press `→` to advance steps; check the nav panel (N) shows the step text.
6. Press `Enter` to hear the current step spoken via TTS.
